ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY...<br>
<br>
A downtown Manhattan specialty health retailer is seeking a full-time Buyer for its Grocery Department.  The ideal candidate will lead a new initiative to refine and hone the store's center grocery, refrigerated and frozen sections to carry products which meet specific criteria of being organic, non-GMO, vegan, paleo, local, gluten-free and/or a number of other special designations.  The candidate will independently oversee and be solely responsible for negotiating, buying, receiving, merchandising, and, managing stock personnel. The ideal candidate will have the unique opportunity to lead and shape the initiative of the Grocery Department's metamorphosis and then run it independently going forward. The candidate's beliefs and values must be in line with the company's strategy of re-positioning the store into a destination shopping experience for those discriminating New Yorkers seeking high-quality, healthful and unique products.  For this reason, the candidate must be very well informed of natural foods market trends, have existing relationships with vendors and producers, and, be in-the-know of new products coming onto the market. The ideal candidate will also work seamlessly with other departments to cross-merchandise and collaborate with the goal of providing a fully integrated shopping experience and opportunity for our customers. From scouting new products, negotiating pricing directly with vendors, managing personnel, visually merchandising new products, and best of all, working in an industry you love, this position is a unique opportunity for the right candidate to further develop and sharpen their already wide range of business skills.  If you believe that you might be the right fit for the position, then please get in touch to learn more about the position and company.  We would love the opportunity to meet with you.  <br>
<br>
ABOUT THE COMPANY...<br>
Elm Drugs + Elm Health is a premier organic grocery &amp; juice bar, vitamin market, purveyor of natural body and personal care products, and, traditional pharmacy all rolled into a single retail experience. Our mission is to nurture and promote a healthy lifestyle within our community by offering a curated selection of high quality, healthful, unique and often hard-to-find products pulled from all schools of integrative health and thought. We are conveniently located at the crossroads of the West Village and Chelsea at 56 Seventh Avenue between West 13th and 14th Streets.<br>
<br>
ABOUT YOU...<br>
Candidates should have the following qualifications:<br>
-2 years' experience in grocery buying/receiving, or equivalent experience <br>
- Must be able to demonstrate excellent verbal and written communications skills and must be verse in use of email, other electronic communication tools, and, use of the internet<br>
-Proficiency with MS Excel and Word, and, Google Drive (Sheets, Docs, etc.)<br>
-ability to prioritize and multi-task, with a requisite sense of urgency<br>
-ability to lead, manage and delegate tasks to stock-persons <br>
-comfort with basic and retail math (addition, subtraction, division) <br>
-willingness to work both independently and as part of a close-knit team <br>
-reliable, punctual, professional, no drama, and fun-loving! <br>
<br>
GET IN TOUCH...<br>
Please submit your resume and make it attention to Ken.  Please make sure to include your contact info. I look forward to meeting you!<br>
    </section>

